ListOfStreams<T> - Class in Network
This is a superclass for ListOfStreamsCached and ListOfStreamsUncached.
ListOfStreams() - Constructor for class Network.ListOfStreams
 
ListOfStreamsCached<T> - Class in Network
This class maintains an unordered list of items which can either be given explicitely, or be provided on demand by streams.
The list can only be accessed by means of an iterator or a stream.
The idea of this class is to provide a common interface (iterator or stream) to sources of objects, which can come from wherever the streams get them, even from a remote url.
ListOfStreamsCached() - Constructor for class Network.ListOfStreamsCached
 
ListOfStreamsCached.StreamIterator - Class in Network
This iterator at first iterates through the cache, and then allows the streams' threads to add new items to the cache (only one when it is needed.)
ListOfStreamsUncached<T> - Class in Network
This class can maintain a list of items together with a list of streams for supplying new items.
The streams provide new items only when necessary.
